metadata.name: Gnarly #3
metadata.description:
Gnarly is an interactive nft game.

Fly across the city with your hoverboard and avoid the obstacles.

Each iteration will generate a totally different character to play!

Don't forget to collect the coins and eat pizza to recover your health!
You can also collect the sandclocks to slow down the time!

Use the touch/mouse or enter/space keys to jump (you can even double jump!)

Press S to save a screenshot of the game!

metadata.name: A Stroll through the Garden #58
metadata.description:
Exploring the medium, physical, digital, made with AI, is an endless and exciting walk through a garden full of discoveries and hidden corners.

The choice of linocut aesthetics is connected with the personal background as an artist who worked with graphic techniques, childhood memories and feelings of trees deprived of their leaves in winter.

Thanks to YulikolaY for getting the code ready for production.

Made with love, AI and p5.js code

January, 2023

metadata.name: Tesseract #399
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.

metadata.name: SquareCuts #79
metadata.description:

metadata.name: Morphing Convictions #122
metadata.description:
Everyday we move on by relying on our convictions. Their immutability often helps us take decisions or take shelter but can sometimes clash with the unknown, the different and the new. They can then crack, crumble and mutate. To change your convictions means changing the kind of person you want to be. It means changing your self-identity. And that is not just hard, it is scary. And beautiful.

Morphing Convictions is a piece that exists through two kind of outputs : Posters and Scenes. Posters are focusing on the contemplation of details and movements of a morphing conviction while the Scenes are interactive little worlds where you can explore a conviction in it's environment.

Please open in live mode to enjoy a much better experience.

Controls :

Posters & Scenes
• Click anywhere to enable audio.
• Press M to toggle mute.
• Press F to toggle the fullscreen mode.
• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

Scenes only
• Drag and scroll to rotate and zoom.
• Click on objects, some might react.

———————

Morphing Convictions by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity

metadata.name: Rite of Passage #237
metadata.description:
In life, we all take different paths, different rites of passage, and while the end is all that's ever true, we will still all view it and experience it in very different ways, like that masterpiece hanging on the wall at the end of our gallery visit. 
  

There are always things that we will never have the power to change, but at the same time, we determine the route, we influence the journey, we can choose the person we want to be. We'll look back on memories, we'll have regrets, and we'll think about what could have been - but unlike this artwork, in the end we won't be able to change the final output by simply pressing a number - so live well and be happy my friends. 

---------------------

Generative artwork by Sykcolo / @sykcoloart

Primary sale proceeds:
50% to Processing Foundation
50% to Savepakistan

Royalties:
50% to the original minter
50% to artist (me)

Press '2' to '4' to see what could have been + increase pixel density. 
Press 's' to save

Details:

150 hand-picked colour pallets (thanks to @SteveMakerspace for colour selection method)
2 Frame types
4 Art types
2 Times of day (light or dark background)
